laboratory_examinations.findings: The liver shows no evidence of focal lesions or ductal abnormality. There is no evidence of intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilation. There is no gallbladder wall thickening or pericholecystic fluid. The common bile duct measures 7 mm. The portal vein demonstrates normal hepatopetal flow.
